snippet.textDisplay:
This Will probably be burried, However I'd like to say my story with this lovely series.

A good friend of mine (M) and myself (S) had taken to attempting to use the lovely voices from DBZA.
M focused on Nappa, Android 13 and Tien. I had focused on Krillin, Yamcha, Vegeta, Sixteen and Gohan, still practicing on Freeza and Raditz.

M: (As Nappa): Hey! Vegeta!
S: (As Vegeta): ...God dammit what now Nappa?
M: I made a new drink Vegeta! Its called... "Snappa~" he said with a showy voice
S: I'm listening...
M: We've got all sorts of flavors! From Wolf Tang Spit to Saibaman blast!
S: trying my hardest not to laugh Wh-what? Thats ridiculous who would even fund this?!
M: Your hot wife.
S: ... excuse m-
M: Ahh! But thats not what I'm here for Veggie! I came to promote a new flavor, tell me what you think, Its for our weaker tastebuded customers, Its got the same taste as Saibaman blast, but its MUCH weaker...
S: Alright, and what is the flavor called...?
M: I call it... "Raditzberry~!"
S: genuinely losing it Thats astounding! N-now. Whats your strongest flavor?
M: Uhh... I-I should g-
S: Grabbing him What. Is. The. Flavor.
M: ...Kakacarrot...
S: sigh of defeat God... dammit Nappa...

This show wouldn't have given my friend and I these little stupid interactions with the characters that have wooed us to this day.

Thank you Team Fourstar. You guys are all amazing people and I wish you good luck for all your future shows.

-Loyal Sub, SylverGardevoir

I hate to see this end. You guys have heard this 1,000 times but I hope it never loses its meaning. I discovered your channel during the deepest depression of my life. You guys were the only thing that made me laugh, I can never thank you all enough. Please never stop the great work you’re all doing.
P.S. can we go ahead and get Black/White Nuzlocke?

snippet.textDisplay: every journey must come to and end. Personally, id started watching dbz A when i was 14 yrs old, hardly a teenager. I remember entering the Team4star's main web to watch the episodes. of course i watch episode 60 part 2 the very same day it was online, as fully grown adult, still laughing as hard as when a i was a little kid who love Akira Toriyama's work, and by extension, your work guys.- many things change in my life for sure, but yours work, which was on the going for so long, was like a rope tied up way back to my childhood. How can i or any of your fans angry with this decision? You had been with us for 12 fucking years, what else can we ask you guys to do? There is no need for any kind of apologies. Just an oportunity for us to tell you guys how wonderful, creative and hilarious your work was / is. THANK YOU ALL Team4Star.

snippet.textDisplay:
Ultimately, I’m not angry - just really sad that something I love is ending.

That being said, in no way do I want you to feel guilty for this decision. You guys have dedicated so many years of your life to DBZA and as sad as I am to see it go, I think you left it off at a good point. Episode 60 definitely did have an air of finality to it. If it must come to an end, I’m glad it ended on a good note, the characters at peace and looking toward the future.

Thank you, really. This series was wonderful and funny and sometimes heart wrenching. I’ll miss it dearly, but I’ll always look back on it fondly.

I wish you guys the best in any future endeavors!!

snippet.textDisplay: At first I was really let down and disappointed that the series wasn't going to continue. But once I seen the expression of disappointment and at one point failure on your face thats when I Realized that this show meant more to you than it ever did to me (and I absolutely adore dbza) so I want to thank you for all of the laughs that you have provided me and my brother with over the years. I want to thank you for all of your hard work that all of you have put in. I will probably be quoting this show even when I am old and decrepit (if I make it that far) what an amazing run and and amazing time I have had watching the series over and over and over.... I would love to see the stuff that is still in the pipeline. I will always be a fan! And please don't feel like you let your fanbase down. What you did with a childhood fantasy show stamps the proof of your comedic genius! So from the bottom of my heart I thank you. And I no homo love you! Best of luck with your future endeavors. DBZA4LIFE
